The paper deals with neural networks and optimization, which are topics commonly found in the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). The use of exponential and logarithmic activation functions suggests a focus on neural network architectures (cs.NE). The application of the proposed methodology to physical systems implies a connection to control theory and systems engineering (cs.SY). The use of convex optimization and geometric programming suggests a focus on optimization algorithms (cs.AI) and mathematical programming (cs.DS).
